member.summary: Saves a into the Patient Manager database.
member.param: The to create or update in the Database.
member.returns: The saved
member.remarks: If the doesn't exists in the database a new record will be inserted. The primary key will be updated in the returned entity. If the already exists in the database it will be updated. The ModifiedBy and ModifiedAt will be updated in the returned entity. This method implements optimistic locking based on a timestamp check, The Modification Date in the update entity must match the current row on the database. If the Update Timestamp does not match a database exception is raised.

member.name: M:iSOFT.ANZ.PatientManagerServiceLibrary.IUserService.UserCopy(iSOFT.ANZ.PatientManagerServiceLibrary.SecurityToken,iSOFT.ANZ.PatientManagerServiceLibrary.User,System.String)
member.summary: Creates a new iPM user based on an exisiting iPM User.
member.param: a partially populated user objects with the details of the new iPM user to be created
a string that contains the iPM UserId
member.remarks:
The newUser object must contain a Code(User ID) and a Password. The newUser object will also be checked for a Clinician Oid(Refno) or Code (Main Ident). A check is done on the following fields to see if they are populated, where they are empty they will be populated from the exisiting iPM user: UserName, Department, Email, PhoneNumber The remainder of the user setting will be taken from the existing iPM user.
The following fields must be blank or 0: UsersOid UserWorkStations.UswrkOid UserWorkStations.UsersOid UserRoles.UsersOid
member.returns: A populated object for the new iPM user
